│   ↓                                                                 │
│ QEMU VIRTIO-BLK DEVICE                                             │
│   1. Trap doorbell write                      ~100 ns              │
│   2. virtio_queue_notify()                    ~50 ns               │
│   3. virtqueue_pop() (pop descriptors)        ~500 ns              │
│   4. GPA → HVA translation                    ~200 ns              │
│   5. Read data from guest memory              ~100 ns              │
│   6. Submit to block layer (AIO/io_uring)     ~1000 ns             │
│   7. Wait for I/O completion                  ~100,000 ns (100μs)  │
│   8. Write data to guest memory               ~100 ns              │
│   9. virtqueue_push()                         ~200 ns              │
│   10. virtio_notify()                         ~50 ns               │
│   11. MSI-X interrupt                         ~200 ns              │
│   ↓                                                                 │
│   Total QEMU-side: ~102,500 ns (excluding block I/O)              │
│   ↓                                                                 │
│   INTERRUPT HANDLER IN GUEST                                       │
│   1. VM Entry                                   ~1000 ns          │
│   2. ISR: read used ring                       ~20 ns              │
│   3. Process completion                        ~50 ns              │
│   4. Wake up waiting process                   ~200 ns             │
│   ↓                                                                 │
│   Total Guest ISR: ~1270 ns                                        │
│   ↓                                                                 │
│ GUEST APPLICATION RESUMES                                          │
│   read() returns                                                  │
│   ↓                                                                 │
│   ~100 ns                                                          │
│   ↓                                                                 │
│   TOTAL: ~104,000 ns (~10,000 IOPS)                                │
│   Wait... what about 1M IOPS?                                     │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

The 1M IOPS Barrier

Why we can't get 1M IOPS from this path:

1. VM Exit Cost: ~1000 ns × 2 (in/out) = 2000 ns
2. QEMU Processing: ~1000 ns per I/O
3. Block I/O: ~100,000 ns (actual disk access)

To reach 1M IOPS (1000 ns per I/O), we need:

1. Polling Mode: Eliminate VM exits by guest busy-waiting
2. Userspace I/O: vhost-user bypasses QEMU
3. NVMe: Direct hardware access (no block layer overhead)

