# Device responds to both legacy and modern
# Guest can choose which to use
```

3. Option C: Backport Driver
   · Provide updated virtio driver for old kernel
   · Backport from upstream Linux
4. Option D: Upgrade Guest
   · Recommend RHEL/CentOS 7+ or Ubuntu 16.04+

Principal Answer: "I'd choose Option B for compatibility while Option C for long-term support. But I'd also instrument the device to report which mode is used to help customers identify their issue."

</details>

