Section 3.2: Transport Layer Deep Dive

PCI Transport (virtio-pci)

PCI Configuration Space Layout:

```
Offset  | Field                       | Description
--------|-----------------------------|------------------------------------------
0x00    | Device ID (0x1040-0x104F)   | Vendor-specific device ID
0x02    | Vendor ID (0x1AF4)          | Red Hat virtio vendor ID
0x04    | Status (PCIE)               | PCIe capability flags
0x10    | BAR0 (Common config)        | Virtio common configuration
0x14    | BAR1 (Device config)        | Device-specific configuration
0x18    | BAR2 (ISR status)           | Interrupt status
0x1C    | BAR4 (Notification)         | Doorbell for each queue
```

Virtio-PCI Modern Capabilities:

```c
// Modern virtio PCI capability structure
struct virtio_pci_cap {
    uint8_t  cap_vndr;    // PCI_CAP_ID_VNDR (0x09)
    uint8_t  cap_next;    // Next capability pointer
    uint8_t  cap_len;     // Capability length
    uint8_t  cfg_type;    // Common, ISR, Device, Notification
    uint32_t bar;         // BAR index
    uint32_t offset;      // Offset within BAR
    uint32_t length;      // Capability length
};
```

Bar 0 - Common Configuration:

```c
struct virtio_pci_common_cfg {
    uint32_t device_feature_select;   // Select feature word
    uint32_t device_feature;          // Device features (read-only)
    uint32_t driver_feature_select;   // Select feature word
    uint32_t driver_feature;          // Driver features (write)
    uint16_t msix_config;             // MSI-X vector for config changes
    uint16_t num_queues;              // Number of queues (read-only)
    uint8_t  device_status;           // Status bits
    uint8_t  config_generation;       // Config change counter
    // Queue-specific fields
    uint16_t queue_select;            // Select queue index
    uint16_t queue_size;              // Size of selected queue
    uint16_t queue_msix_vector;       // MSI-X vector for queue
    uint16_t queue_enable;            // Enable/disable queue
    uint16_t queue_notify_off;        // Offset in BAR4 for doorbell
    uint64_t queue_desc;              // GPA of descriptor table
    uint64_t queue_avail;             // GPA of available ring
    uint64_t queue_used;              // GPA of used ring
};
```

MMIO Transport (virtio-mmio)

Used in:

· ARM architecture (Qualcomm, Apple)
· Embedded systems without PCI
· RISC-V (SiFive)

MMIO Register Map:

```c
struct virtio_mmio {
    uint32_t MagicValue;          // 0x74726976 ("virt")
    uint32_t Version;             // 0x2 (virtio 1.0+)
    uint32_t DeviceID;            // Which device (block, net, etc.)
    uint32_t VendorID;            // 0x1AF4 (Red Hat)
