Q25: How does virtio handle ARM vs x86 differences?

<details>
<summary><b>Answer</b></summary>

ARM Differences:

1. Memory Ordering: ARM is weakly ordered
   · Must use explicit memory barriers (dmb, dsb)
   · Without barriers, reordering can corrupt data
2. Cache Coherency: ARM requires explicit cache maintenance
   · dc cvac (clean cache) before device reads
   · dc ivac (invalidate) before driver reads
3. Transport: ARM often uses MMIO (not PCI)
   · No PCI config space
   · Direct memory-mapped registers
4. Page Size: ARM uses 4KB/16KB/64KB
   · Virtio must align to guest page size

</details>

