Q33: Explain the memory barriers required in virtio.

<details>
<summary><b>Answer</b></summary>

Memory Barrier Types:

1. wmb() - Write Memory Barrier:
   · Ensures all previous writes are visible before later writes
   · Used before updating avail->idx (driver)
   · Used before updating used->idx (device)
2. rmb() - Read Memory Barrier:
   · Ensures all previous reads complete before later reads
   · Used before reading avail->idx (device)
   · Used before reading used->idx (driver)
3. mb() - Full Memory Barrier:
   · Both read and write ordering
   · Used in critical sections

When to use barriers:

```c
// Driver writes descriptors
desc->addr = buffer;
desc->len = size;
wmb();  // Write barrier
avail->ring[avail->idx] = desc_idx;
wmb();  // Write barrier
avail->idx++;

// Device reads descriptors
rmb();  // Read barrier
desc_idx = avail->ring[avail->idx];
rmb();  // Read barrier
// Now read descriptor
```

Architecture differences:

· x86: Strong ordering, barriers mostly no-ops
· ARM: Weak ordering, barriers are critical
· PowerPC: Very weak ordering, many barriers needed

</details>

